Files and Directory Operations

dir – Lists files and folders in a directory.
cd – Changes the current directory.
copy, xcopy, robocopy – Copies files and directories.
del – Deletes files.
mkdir / rmdir – Creates or removes directories

Get-Item -Path "C:\Path\to\your\folder"

wildcard character (*) to display all properties.
Get-Item -Path "C:\Path\To\Your\Folder" | Select-Object *

Select-Object cmdlet with the Property parameter. 
Get-Item -Path "C:\Path\To\Your\Folder" | Select-Object Name, CreationTime, LastWriteTime

hidden files you can specify the "Hidden" attribute
Get-ChildItem -Path "C:\Path\To\Your\Folder" -Attributes Hidden


Get-FileHash -Path "C:\Path\To\Your\File.txt"

Find all .txt files a folder:
Get-ChildItem -Path "C:\Data" -Filter "*.txt" 

Find all notes.txt files its subdirectories
Get-ChildItem -Path "C:\temp\" -Filter "Notes.txt" -Recurse



